d><td>Once per encounter, character may gain the benefits of an  eligible Combat Edge for five rounds.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mighty Blow]{Mighty Blow}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, Fighting d8</td><td>On first successful @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll, double damage when dealt a Joker.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Missile Deflection]{Missile Deflection}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Fighting d10</td><td>Ranged attackers use character's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.idEEdHIeNSogKRGm]{Parry} as base TN.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nerves of Steel]{Nerves of Steel}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d8</td><td>Ignore one level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Nerves of Steel]{Improved Nerves of Steel}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Nerves of Steel</td><td>Ignore up to two levels of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.No Mercy]{No Mercy}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S</td><td>+2 damage when spending a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll damage.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Opportunistic]{Opportunistic}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V</td><td>A  Joker adds +4 to Trait and damage rolls rahter than +2.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Reload]{Rapid Reload}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Shooting d6</td><td>Reduce the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} value of a weapon by 1.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Shot]{Rapid Shot}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Shooting d6</td><td>Increase @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for one @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack per turn.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Rapid Shot]{Improved Rapid Shot}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Rapid Shot</td><td>Increase @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for up to two @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks per turn.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Roar]{Roar}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8</td><td>May make an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.NWzjRjwyVKIngdAM]{Intimidation} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.z8VbTEJUItMTSxNw]{Test} in a Cone Template.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Savagery]{Savagery}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Fighting d8</td><td>+4 damage with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.xJpg68BZwGvRe0pQ]{Wild Attacking} rather than +2.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Assassin</td><td>Replaces assassin's +2 damage with d6 that aces.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sneak Attack]{Improved Sneak Attack}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sneak Attack</td><td>May sneak attack a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted} foe.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steady Hands]{Steady Hands}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td><td>Ignore @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform} penalty; reduce running penalty to –1.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steal Away]{Steal Away}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8, Stealth d6</td><td>The hero can make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} to hide when withdrawing.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Stunning Blow]{Stunning Blow}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, St d8</td><td>Foe must make a Vigor roll or be @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.D2Z390QR9ROJwxMy]{Stunned} if @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.fN6mUVj1Lkxtr9HE]{Shaken} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.ih5SJibOjuXkxey4]{Wounded} with a blunt weapon.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sucker Punch]{Sucker Punch}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d6, Fighting d8, First Strike</td><td>If the hero succeeds on a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}, they recieve a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sunder]{Sunder}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, St d8</td><td>Attacker adds +d6 damage when trying to break things.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, St d8, Fighting d8</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll at –2 to hit all targets in weapon’s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}, no more than once per turn.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sweep]{Improved Sweep}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sweep</td><td>As above, but ignore the –2 penalty.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, d8 in related skill</td><td>+1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} total with a specific weapon; +1 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Parry} while weapon is readied.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Trademark Weapon]{Improved Trademark Weapon}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Trademark Weapon</td><td>The attack and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Parry} bonus increases to +2.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trick Shot]{Trick Shot}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Athletics or Shooting d8</td><td>Character may make foe resist with Smarts instead of Agility with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.z8VbTEJUItMTSxNw]{Test}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Hero]{True Hero}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, WC, Iron Jaw</td><td>When the hero would get @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}, they get a free @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Two-Weapon Fighting]{Two-Weapon Fighting}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td><td>Make one extra @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll with a second melee weapon in the off-hand at no @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wrestler]{Wrestler}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A or St d6, Fighting d6</td><td>Make make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting] roll rather than @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Crushing} damage is increased to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} + d4.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Takedown Move]{Takedown Move}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Wrestler</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Push]{Push} moves are opposed at a –2 (–4 on a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Leadership Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.A Few Good Men]{A Few Good Men}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Inspire, Sm d8 , Battle d10</td><td>In @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, add one more Token to force calculations.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Board 'Em]{Board 'Em}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Command, Athletics d8</td><td>+4 to group @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls to grapple an enemy vessel.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in Battle]{Born in Battle}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls, and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Command}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6</td><td>+1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} recovery rolls.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command Presence]{Command Presence}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td><td>Increase Command Range to 10″ (20 yards)</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Coordinated Firepower]{Coordinated Firepower}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sm d6, Command, Athletics or Shooting d8</td><td>The hero adds a flat +2 attack bonus for additional ranged attacks for those within command range. Additional bonus damage on raises.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cry Havoc!]{Cry Havoc!}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Fervor, Battle d10</td><td>In @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the character may declare a charge that will cause his enemy to lose one extra token.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Death before Dishonor]{Death before Dishonor}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Hold the Line, Battle d8</td><td>In @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero gains +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} when rolling for Morale.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Drop!]{Drop!}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command, Notice d6</td><td>Allows to hero to command allies to drop @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fanaticism]{Fanaticism}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fervor</td><td>Those in Command Range gain +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fervor]{Fervor}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sp d8, Command</td><td>Extras in range add +1 to their @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Help Me!]{Help Me!}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td><td>When an enemy moves adjacent to the hero, the hero may call for help acting as if they were on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hold the Line!]{Hold the Line!}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command</td><td>+1 to  @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} in Command Range.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire]{Inspire}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Command</td><td>Once per turn, the hero may roll his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} skill to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} one type of Trait roll, and apply it to everyone in Command Range.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master and Commander]{Master and Commander}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Sm d8, Command, Boating d10, Intimidation d8, must be sole captain</td><td>Crews get +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Leader]{Natural Leader}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8, Command</td><td>Leadership Edges now apply to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Breaker]{Siege Breaker}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td><td>In @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when conducting a siege with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Mentality]{Siege Mentality}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td><td>In @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when defending in a siege with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tactician]{Tactician}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d6</td><td>Draw an extra @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each turn that may be assigned to any allied @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} in Command Range.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Tactician]{Master Tactician}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Tactician</td><td>Draw and distribute two extra @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} instead of one.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Power Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adaptable Caster]{Adaptable Caster}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (See List), arcane skill d6</td><td>The trappings can be changed on the powers for 1 Power Point.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Battle Magic]{Battle Magic}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, AB (Any) arcane skill d10</td><td>The mage may cast battle magic.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Blood Magic]{Blood Magic}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Any), evil</td><td>The mage recovers d6 Power Points when directly causing a wound to a sapient creature.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channeling]{Channeling}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB</td><td>Reduce Power Point cost by 1 with a raise on the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Activation]{Activation} roll.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Concentration]{Concentration}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td><td>Double duration of all non-Instant powers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Craft Arcane Device]{Craft Arcane Device}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any but Psionics), Arcana or Repair d6</td><td>Allows user to create arcane devices to share with others imbued with a single power.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Dragonmarks}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Special</td><td>Grants a dragonmark with various auto-activating powers in different packages. See @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Dragonmarks}</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Greater Dragonmarks}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Special</td><td>Greats a greater dragonmark to an existing dragonmark. Adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modificers, and additional powers(s). See @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Greater Dragonmarks}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Epic Mastery]{Epic Mastery}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, AB (Any) arcane skill d6</td><td>The caster may use Epic Power Modifiers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Familiar]{Familiar}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (See List)</td><td>Caster gains a small pet that grants her 5 Power Points and other abilities.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers]{Favored Powers}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any) arcane skill d8</td><td>Caster may ignore 2 points of any penalties when activating two chosen powers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Finely Tuned]{Finely Tuned}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Craft Arcane Device, Repair d8</td><td>Reduce the cost of creating @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any or MP (Any), Vow (to your Deity)</td><td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Artificer]{Master Artificer}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AB (Artificer) or Craft Arcane Device, Arcana or Repair d10</td><td>Artificer gains an additional 250 gp progress for each success and raise when making magical items.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Mystic Powers}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Special</td><td>Grants various, auto-activating powers in different packages. See @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers]{Mystic Powers}</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB</td><td>Your character knows two new powers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Points]{Power Points}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td><td>Grants 5 additional Power Points.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Pool]{Power Pool}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, two AB (Any), both arcane skills d8</td><td>Allows the hero with more than one Arcane Background to merge the Power Points from each.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Power Surge]{Power Surge}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, AB (Any), arcane skill d8</td><td>The hero recovers 10 Power Points when his action card is a Joker.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Silent Caster]{Silent Caster}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (See List)</td><td>The mage does not need to speak to cast.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soul Drain]{Soul Drain}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8, AB (Any) or MP (Any)</td><td>Take a level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} to recover 5 Power Points, or 2 to recover 10.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Professional Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ace]{Ace}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8</td><td>Character may spend @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for his vehicle and ignores up to 2 points of penalties.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Acrobat]{Acrobat}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Athletics d8</td><td>Free reroll on acrobatic @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} attempts.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Acrobat]{Combat Acrobat}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Acrobat</td><td>−1 to hit with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{ranged and melee attacks}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin]{Assassin}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Fighting d6, Stealth d8</td><td>+2 to damage foes when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Vulnerable} or assassin has @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.wmmbjJLJfMXwMcKf]{The Drop}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in the Saddle]{Born in the Saddle}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Riding d6</td><td>Gain one free reoll on all @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} rolls and increase the mount's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} by 2 and its running die one step.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Entertainer]{Entertainer}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Performance d8</td><td>+1 to any two:  @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}  skills.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Explorer]{Explorer}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d6, Survival d8</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Survival roll to draw an additional card when using the Travel rule and choose between the two types; increases party’s Travel Times by 10%.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Mount]{Fast Mount}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Riding d6</td><td>Mount and dismount as a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hidden Strike]{Hidden Strike}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Fighting d6, Stealth d8</td><td>+2 to damage foes when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or assassin has @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inquisitive]{Inquisitive}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d8, Lore d8</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} and certain types of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Jack-Of-All-Trades]{Jack-of-All-Trades}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d10</td><td>Gain d4 in a skill (or d6 with a raise) until replaced.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Knight]{Knight}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, St d8, V d8, Fighting d8, Riding d8</td><td>The knight is gifted with the tools of his trade. He also gains a +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when dealing with good causes.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Storyteller]{Master Storyteller}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8, Persuasion d8</td><td>The storyteller rolls d8's for Glory rolls instead of d6's.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Legendary Storyteller]{Legendary Storyteller}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, Master Storyteller</td><td>The storyteller gains a d8 Glory for each raise after the first.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mount]{Mount}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Riding d6</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The hero gains a mount that becomes more powerful as he gains Ranks.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monster Hunter]{Monster Hunter}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d6</td><td>The hero is immune to the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks of one type of creature. </td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mr Fix It]{Mr. Fix It}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Repair d8</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} rolls, half the time required with a raise.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Poisoner]{Poisoner}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Healing, Science or Science</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The character creates poisons in half the time and contact poisons last 12 hours instead of four.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rope Monkey]{Rope Monkey}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, A d8, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d10</td><td>The sailor can swing among the rigging to move around a ship or canopy. They may also make an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll if they fall to take half damage.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scholar]{Scholar}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Research d8</td><td>+2 to any one “knowledge” skill.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scout]{Scout}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Survival d6</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Notice roll at +2 to detect traps, secret doors, etc., in stone.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ship's Carpenter]{Ship's Carpenter}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Boating d6, Repair d8</td><td>The sailor can repair wounds to a ship without a dry dock.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soldier]{Soldier}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, S d6, V d6</td><td>Strength is one die type higher for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Min Str}. Reroll @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} rolls when resisting environmental @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Stone Cunning]{Stone Cunning}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Repair d6</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Notice roll at +2 to detect traps, secret doors, etc., in stone.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Thief]{Thief}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, A d8, Stealth d6, Thievery d6</td><td>+1 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in urban environments.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Repair d6</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Automatic Notice roll to detect a trap within 5” (10 yards); she and allies ignore 2 points of Evasion penalties to avoid them; ignores up to 2 points of Thievery penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Troubadour]{Troubadour}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Common Knowledge d6, Performance d8</td><td>Add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls; may use @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} in place of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} for Leadership Edges or Edges that require @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Uncanny Reflexes]{Uncanny Reflexes}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, A d8, Athletics d8</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ignores usual –2 penalty to Evade and may Evade area effect attacks that don’t normally allow it.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Woodsman]{Woodsman}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6, Survival d8</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in the wilds.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Social Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bolster]{Bolster}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>May remove @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable} state after a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, N, Sp d8</td><td>The hero may freely give her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to others.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Connections]{Connections}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td><td>Contacts provide aid or other favors once per session.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Deceptive]{Deceptive}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sm d8</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Character may make foe resist with Smarts or Spirit when making a Smarts or Spirit-based Test.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Menacing]{Menacing}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, See Text</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Provoke]{Provoke}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Intimidation or Persuasion d6</td><td>May “provoke” foes with a raise on a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll. See text.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} d8</td><td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} with an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reliable]{Reliable}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Retort]{Retort}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Intimidation d6</td><td>A raise when resisting a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attack makes the foe @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skullduggery]{Skullduggery}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Deception d8</td><td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Streetwise]{Streetwise}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and criminal networking.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Willed]{Strong Willed}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>+2 to resist @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts or Spirit}-based @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests}.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Will]{Iron Will}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Brave, Strong Willed</td><td>The bonus now applies to resisting and recovery from powers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work The Room]{Work The Room}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>Once per turn, roll a second die when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Supporting} via @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and apply result to additional ally.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work the Crowd]{Work the Crowd}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Work the Room</td><td>As above, but up to twice per turn.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Weird Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aura of Courage]{Aura of Courage}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>All allies within 10\" (20 yards) add +2 to Fear checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the Fear Table.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Bond]{Beast Bond}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td><td>The hero may spend @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} for animals under her control.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Master]{Beast Master}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>Animals like your hero and he has a pet of some sort. See text.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Talker]{Beast Talker}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td><td>The hero can speak with animals/</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Champion]{Champion}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8, Fighting d6</td><td>+2 damage vs. supernaturally evil creatures.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Chi]{Chi}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Martial Warrior</td><td>Once per combat, reroll failed attack, make enemy reroll successful attack, add +d6 to unarmed Fighting attack, or make the opponent @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted or Vulnerable}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 to sense ambushes or similar events.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healer]{Healer}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d8</td><td>+2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, magical or otherwise.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Liquid Courage]{Liquid Courage}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, V d8</td><td>Alcohol increases @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} a die type and ignores one level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; –1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility, Smarts}, and related skills.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scavenger]{Scavenger}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Luck</td><td>May find a needed item once per encounter.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]{Storm Chaser}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Boating or Piloting d8</td><td>+1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during storms. Recieve extra @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Symbiont Mastery]{Symbiont Mastery}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6</td><td>Recieve +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} in battle of wills with sybionts. With symbiont attached, +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d8, Boating or Piloting d8</td><td>+1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}. Recieve extra @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Legendary Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Followers}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L</td><td>The hero has five followers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Home Ground]{Home Ground}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L, Sp d8, AB (Any)</td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per encounter, while on “home ground,” caster may spend a Benny to recover all her Power Points. She may also “sense” the state of her home.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Professional]{Professional}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Max Trait</td><td>The character’s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Expert]{Expert}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Professional in Trait</td><td>The character’s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master]{Master}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L, Expert in Trait</td><td>The character’s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Wild Die} is a d10 with a chosen @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Trait}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">WC, L</td><td>The character gains a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} sidekick.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tough As Nails]{Tough As Nails}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, V d8</td><td>The hero can take four @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Tougher Than Nails}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Tough as Nails, V d12</td><td>The hero can take five @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unstoppable]{Unstoppable}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">WC, L, V d10+, Iron Jaw, Nerves of Steel</span></td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hero has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.wQZawcchhTSC6OPq]{Unstoppable} Monstrous Ability.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Warband]{Warband}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">WC, L, Command, at least two other Leadership Edges, Followers</span></td><td><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Five of the champion’s Followers gain the Resilient ability.</span></td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Weapon Master]{Weapon Master}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Fighting d12</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Parry} increases by +1 and Fighting bonus damage die is d8.</td></tr><tr><td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Arms]{Master of Arms}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, Weapon Master</td><td>Parry increases another +1 and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dealing Damage]{bonus damage} die is d10.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"Arcane Background & Edges","type":"text","_id":"nYQfrgBUoC08iO67","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><h1 class=\"wide\">Arcane Backgrounds</h1><p>There are numerous Arcane Backgrounds avilable in <cite>Savage Eberron</cite>. Review all the backgrounds below for a summary of what kind of heroes use them. These are the backgrounds that are available to be used and in all cases should be used instead of those presented in the <cite>Savage Worlds</cite> core rules.</p><h3>Arcane Background Edges</h3><p>There are two to three additional edges that are specific to each Arcane Background. These are detailed on this table, listed under the associated Arcane Background.</p><h3>Modifications from <cite>Fantasy Companion</cite></h3><p>A number of the edges have been either renamed or modified from what is presented in the <cite>Fantasy Companion</cite>. You can use the <cite>Fantasy Companion</cite> as a guide, but use what is presented here as the final version.</p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Class Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6+</td><td>Heroes that has manifested an Aberrant Dragonmark that falls outside the standard marks of the Dragonmarked Houses.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Alchemist)]{Arcane Background (Alchemist)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Alchemists create potions, oils, elixirs, and other consumables imbued with magical abilities. Alchemists imbue their potions, grenades, and oils with the powers they’ve learned.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Chemist]{Chemist}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Alchemist), Sc d8</td><td>The alchemist's concoctions last one week.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Alchemist]{Master Alchemist}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Alchemist), Sc d10</td><td>The alchemist craft permanent potions at half the cost.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Masters of unlocking magic in everyday objects, artificers are supreme inventors. Creating objects of all kinds that can be used to harness magic.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer's Armor]{Artificer's Armor}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Artificer)</td><td>Modify artificers personal armor with additional effects.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Homunculus]{Homunculus}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Artificer)</td><td>Craft a construct @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf]{Familiar}.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Song mages, bards, or skalds work their magic through the power of their voice and musical instruments.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dirge]{Dirge}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AB (Bard)</td><td>Any enemy within 10\" (20 yards) who spends a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CJOnuNywSJDpO7hK]{Soak} or reroll a Trait or damage roll subtracts 2 from the total.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire Heroics]{inspire Heroics}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Bard), Performance d8</td><td>Bard can spend a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} to gain five Inspiration Tokens, that can be given to others to reroll a Trait or damage roll.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Instrument]{Instrument}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Bard)</td><td>With instrument, the Bard adds +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.WeqRVXtog034GUoR]{Performance} based casting rolls.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>More than mere preachers, clerics serve as emissaries of their gods. These ecclesiastics vow to spread the tenets, knowledge, and truth of their faith.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Cleric)</td><td>The cleric can cast healing at a Range of Spirit and has the Additional Recipients Power Modifier.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Destroy Undead]{Destroy Undead}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Ab (Cleric)</td><td>The cleric can deal 2d6 points of damage to undead in a Large Burst Template.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mercy]{Mercy}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Cleric)</td><td>Cleric can automatically remove @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted, Vulnerable}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.fN6mUVj1Lkxtr9HE]{Shaken}, as an action.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6+</td><td>Druids draw primal magic from the world itself. most druids are swathed in tradition.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Heartwood Staff]{Heartwood Staff}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Druid)</td><td>The druid can create a powerful staff as a weapon.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Form]{True Form}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">s, AB (Druid)</td><td>The druid can speak and cast powers at -2 whil shape changed.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Elementalist)]{Arcane Background (Elementalist)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Elementalists are wielders of the very chaos from which their name is derived. Elementalists know the true power of the chaos that they—and wizards—wield.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Elemental Absorption]{Elemental Absorption}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Elementalist)</td><td>Elementalist gains +2 Toughness while experiencing elemental synergy.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Elemental Master]{Elemental Master}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Elementalist)</td><td>The elementalist can take another element and change powers trappings at will.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Illusionist)]{Arcane Background (Illusionist)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>The illusionist is a master of deception, light, and shadow. Like any magic-user, mage, or wizard, they cast spells, but an illusionists's spells are of a distinctive character, creating figments and phantasms to deceive and trick their foes in creative and interesting ways.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Deadly Illusion]{Deadly Illusion}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Illusionist) Spellcasting d10</td><td>The caster can use Deadly Power modifier for illusions at no additional cost.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Illusion]{Master of Illusion}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Illusionist), Spellcasting d8</td><td>Illusions have Mobility and Sound Power Modifiers at no additional cost.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Infernalist)]{Arcane Background (Infernalist)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Dwellers in darkness, demons from the abyss, or spirits from devilish dimensions are the servants of the infernalist. He conjures them to do his bidding, entrapping or binding these otherworldy entities to fulfill his most arduous tasks and bedevil his foes.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Infernal Armor]{Infernal Armor}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Infernalist)</td><td>The infernalist gains +2 infernal armor.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Khyber's Wrath]{Khyber's Wrath}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Infernalist)</td><td>Infernalist adds +2 to damage from <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Magewright)]{Magewright}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Those who work minor magic into their labors are called magewrights.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Necromancer)]{Arcane Background (Necromancer)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Necromancy explores the cosmic forces of life, death, and undeath. They manipulate the energy that animates all living things.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Soul Jar]{Soul Jar}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">L, AB (Necromancer), Arcana d10</td><td>The necromancer turns undead.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Undead Familiar]{Undead Familiar}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Necromancer)</td><td>The necromancer gains a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf]{Familiar} that is Undead.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Psion)]{Arcane Background (Psion)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Psionic powers spring from sentient minds drawing on a reservoir of mental strength to manipulate matter, read minds, and far more.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mentalist]{Mentalist}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Psion)</td><td>Psions gain +2 on opposed @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Edu9es0KfrPqpjmP]{Psionics} rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psicrystal]{Psicrystal}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Psion)</td><td>The psion has a sentient crystal that is a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf]{Familiar}.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Shaman)]{Arcane Background (Shaman)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6+</td><td>Shamans are magic users that gain their powers through spirits. They are the bridge that connects the material world and the ethereal world. They can cast spells or use the very spirits to help them in and out of combat, so much so, that being surrounded by spirits is a common occurrence for them.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Primal Magic]{Primal Magic}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Shaman)</td><td>Shaman adds =2 to damage from <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> or <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{damage field}</em>. A @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hCxcCUCRxHOWcNGS]{Critical Failure} casuse an explosion.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sacred Fetish]{Sacred Fetish}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Shaman), Faith d8</td><td>The shaman gets a free reoll whenever she fails a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.OfnjSxCc2QxHcIhp]{Faith} roll.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sp d6+</td><td>The hero has innate abilities that don't fit in the any of the other magical backgrounds, such as innate racial magic, or sorcerers.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Power]{Great Power}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">V, Ab (Sorcerer)</td><td>The  sorcerer can send a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} and cast any power available to the sorcerer spell list at -2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SLOGZKFBCI8VAme7]{Spellcasting}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Phenomenal Power]{Phenomenal Power}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AB (Sorcerer)</td><td>The sorcerer can  spend Conviction to cast any power available in the setting at -2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SLOGZKFBCI8VAme7]{Spellcasting}.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Summoner)]{Arcane Background (Summoner)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Summoners have become adept at beckoning animals and monsters from the farthest reaches of the planes. These mages specialize in summoning creatures from the natural world or other planes of existence to bear their burdens for them.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Barding]{Arcane Barding}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Summoner), <em>summon animal</em></td><td>Summoned animals Toughness increased +2.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ferocious Summoning]{Ferocious Summoning}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Summoner), <em>summon monster</em></td><td>Grant any summoned monster one Combat Edge of his rank or lower.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Summoning]{Great Summoning}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AB (Summoner), <em>summon animal, summon monster</em></td><td>Summoner can summon greater creatures.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)]{Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>Warlocks (male) and witches (female) learn their craft from a mix of sources. They might learn one spell from an old wizard’s grimoire, another from their grandmother’s notes, and another from shadowy beings that lurk in the dark woods.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.The Evil Eye]{The Evil Eye}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, AB (Warlock/Witch)</td><td>The witch targets and intelligent being. The target needs to make a Spirit roll -2 to spend a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.The Witching Hour]{The Witching Hour}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Ab (Warlock/Witch)</td><td>The warlock cannot @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hCxcCUCRxHOWcNGS]{Critical Fail} on a roll between midnight and 1. They also get a free @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CJOnuNywSJDpO7hK]{Soak Roll}.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Sm d6+</td><td>These shrewd magic-users research, collect, and covet esoteric knowledge. Some choose to become a master of a particular field of magical study. Others embrace versatility, reveling in the unbounded wonders of all magic</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Inspiration]{Eldritch Inspiration}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">H, AB (Wizard)</td><td>Wizard may spend a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} to cast any power of his Rank or lower.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spellbooks]{Spellbooks}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, AB (Wizard)</td><td>Wizard gets three powers instead of two when taking the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.baxaDqYcVWLczXfl]{New Powers} Edge.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Dragonmarks and Mystic Powers","type":"text","_id":"xL94o0jBMToYz1c9","title":{"show":false,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><h1 class=\"wide\">Dragonmarks &amp; Mystic Powers</h1><p>Below you will find all the edges that deal specifically with Dragonmarks and Mystic Powers.</p><p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You’ll find a summary below.</p><p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Below each Edge is the minimum @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} (see @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Dragonmarked Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Detection]{Mark of Detection}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Half-elf</td><td>Mark of Detection with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait}</em> (@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and any \"knowledge\" based skill only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em> (no Identify), and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em> (poisons and traps only). +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Detection]{Greater Mark of Detection}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Detection</td><td>Mark of Detection adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Finding]{Mark of Finding}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human, Half-orc, or Orc</td><td>Mark of Finding with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait}</em> (@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and any \"knowledge\" based skill only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em>. <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost trait}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</em> have the range of touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Finding]{Greater Mark of Finding}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Finding</td><td>Mark of Finding adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Handling]{Mark of Handling}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td><td>Mark of Handling with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (animals only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy}, </em>and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Animal]{summon animal}</em>. <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait} </em>has the range of touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Animal Handling]{Animal Handling}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Handling]{Greater Mark of Handling}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Handling</td><td>Mark of Handling adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</em> (beasts only).</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Healing]{Mark of Healing}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Halfling</td><td>Mark of Healing with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} </em>(@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{heali, ng}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{survival}, and@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{resurrection}</em>. All powers are touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Healing]{Greater Mark of Healing}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Healing</td><td>Mark of Healing adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and adds the powers <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{Resurrection}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Hospitality]{Mark of Hospitality}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Halfling</td><td>Mark of Hospitality with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item} </em>(Create Food and Weather only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em> (humanoids only), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em> (no Weather), and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{slumber}</em>. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Hospitality]{Greater Mark of Hospitality}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Hospitality</td><td>Mark of Hospitality adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{Plane Shift}</em> (Extra-dimensional space only).</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Making]{Mark of Making}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td><td>Mark of Making with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure item}</em> (not including Create Food and Water), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em> (not including Alignment Sense), and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}.</em> <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/conceal arcana}</em> has a ranch of touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Making]{Greater Mark of Making}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Making</td><td>Mark of Making adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Passage]{Mark of Passage}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td><td>Mark of Passage with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{leaping}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Animal]{summon animal}</em> (mount only). All powers (except <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>) have a range of touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Passage]{Greater Mark of Passage}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Passage</td><td>Mark of Passage adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and adds the powers <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Scribing]{Mark of Scribing}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Gnome</td><td>Mark of Scribing with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Mark]{arcane mark}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{message}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em>. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Scribing]{Greater Mark of Scribing}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Scribing</td><td>Mark of Scribing adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</em> (spoek or written words trappings only).</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Sentinel]{Mark of Sentinel}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Human</td><td>Mark of Sentinel with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>. All powers have the range of touch only. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Sentinel]{Greater Mark of Sentinel}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Sentinel</td><td>Mark of Sentinel adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Shadow]{Mark of Shadow}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Elf</td><td>Mark of Shadow with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em> (no Deadly Illusion). +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Shadow]{Greater Mark of Shadow}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Shadow</td><td>Mark of Shadow adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and adds the powers <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Storm]{Mark of Storm}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Half-elf</td><td>Mark of Storm with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em> (air and water trapping only, not including Damage or Deadly), <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (air and water trapping only), and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em> (air and water trappings only). +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Storm]{Greater Mark of Storm}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Storm</td><td>Mark of Storm adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</em>.</td></tr><tr class=\"highlighted\"><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Warding]{Mark of Warding}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">N, Dwarf</td><td>Mark of Warding with 10 dedicated Power Points to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{sentry}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]{ward}</em>. +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Greater Mark of Warding]{Greater Mark of Warding}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Mark of Warding</td><td>Mark of Warding adds 5 Power Points, Epic Power Modifiers, and adds the powers <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{conceal arcana}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>.</td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Mystic Powers Edges</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Edge</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Requirements</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:60%\">Summary</th></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Barbarian)]{Mystic Powers (Barbarian)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, St d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The barbarian has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Fighting, Strength, Spirit, or Vigor only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>. All have the Self Limitation.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Fighter)]{Mystic Powers (Fighter)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Fighting d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The fighte rhas 10 dedicated Power Points she can use to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Fighting, Shooting, Strength, and Vigor only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>. All have the Self Limitation.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Monk)]{Mystic Powers (Monk)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Athletics d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The monk has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Agility, Athletics, Fighting, and Spirit only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>. All have the Self Limitation.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Paladin)]{Mystic Powers (Paladin)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Sp d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The paladin has 10 dedicated Power Points she can use to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Fighting and Spirit only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{sanctuary},</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>. All but healing have the Self Limitation.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Ranger)]{Mystic Powers (Ranger)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Survival d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The ranger has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>Beast friend, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Athletics, Shooting, and Survival only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em>. All but entangle and beast friend have the Self Limitation.</td></tr><tr><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Rogue)]{Mystic Powers (Rogue)}</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">S, Thievery d8</td><td style=\"width:60%\">The rogue has 10 dedicated Power Points she can use to cast <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} (Athletics, Stealth, and Thievery only), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock},</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{wall walker}</em>. All have the Self Limitation.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":700000,"name":"Advancement","type":"text","_id":"saneNpHYSTivNRYE","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><div><h1 class=\"wide\">Advancement</h1></div><p>One of the many great aspects of roleplaying games is advancing your character, watching her grow from a Novice adventurer to a Legendary hero.</p><p>Advances are granted by the Dungeon Master at the end of some game \"sessions\" (about 4–5 hours of play).</p><p>An Advance lets a character make one of the adjustments listed below. Remember that no @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Trait} may be raised above its maximum (usually d12 unless modified by an ancestral ability, Edge, etc).</p><ul><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Attribute:</span> Increase one attribute one die type. This option may be taken only once per Rank. Legendary characters may raise an attribute no more than every fourth Advance, up to the ancestral or class maximum.</li><li><p><span class=\"list-heading\">Skills:</span> Increase a skill that is equal to or greater than its linked attribute one die type;<br />OR increase two skills that are lower than their linked attributes by one die type each (including new skills the character didn’t have before at d4). You cannot increase the same skill twice with the same Advance.</p></li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Edge:</span> Gain a new Edge. You should have a story-based reason to take a Background or a core @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Setting Edges]{Class Edge}. You can’t become a barbarian overnight, after all. Gaining these @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Edges]{Edges} should usually take years or some dramatic change in the character’s life, and should only be done with the Dungeon Master’s permission. Core Class Edges and core @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Setting Edges]{Prestige Edges} are also limited to one per Rank. Legendary characters may choose a core Class Edge (or Prestige Edge) no more than every fourth Advance.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Buy Off a Hindrance:</span> Permanently remove a Minor @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Hindrances]{Hindrance}, or reduce a Major Hindrance to a Minor (if possible). The player and DM should work out how and when this happens. Perhaps the shocking death of an ally triggers a change in attitude, the hero puts real effort into improving harmful behavior, or seeks professional help during @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Downtime]{Downtime}.</li></ul><h2>Rank</h2><p>“Ranks” reflect a character’s competence and experience. They provide balance between players and grant access to more powerful abilities as one “Advances.” A character begins at Novice Rank and works upward from there. Advances are given out after one or more game sessions. The DM has more detailed information in the Advancement section @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{here}.</p><p>Only player characters use Ranks— Dungeon Master-controlled characters and creatures don’t (we’ll tell you more about this later).</p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"2\">Rank</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Advances</th><th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Rank</th></tr><tr><td class=\"centered\">0–3</td><td class=\"centered\">Novice</td></tr><tr><td class=\"centered\">4–7</td><td class=\"centered\">Seasoned</td></tr><tr><td class=\"centered\">8–11</td><td class=\"centered\">Veteran</td></tr><tr><td class=\"centered\">12–15</td><td class=\"centered\">Heroic</td></tr><tr><td class=\"centered\">16+</td><td class=\"centered\">Legendary</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Starting With Experienced Characters</h3><p>If the Dungeon Master wants to start a game with more experienced characters, or you're making a replacement for a fallen hero, you should still make a Novice starting profile and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advance} it from there. This ensures characters are balanced just as if they had gained experience normally.</p><p>Additional goods, equipment, or other assets must be determined by the Dungeon Master. As a quick rule of thumb, Seasoned heroes have 10,000 gold pieces worth of goods and magic items, Veteran characters get 40,000, Heroic 150,000, and Legendary 500,000.</p><h2>Advancement Pace</h2><p>How fast characters Advance in <cite>Savage Eberron</cite> depends on the campaign.</p><ul><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Official Adventure Paths:</span> These epic tales tell the Dungeon Master when to give the party an Advance. They typically start at Novice Rank and end at Legendary+, spreading improvements along as the story advances to different stages.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Short Campaigns:</span> If you’re running a campaign of your own creation and expect it to last 10 sessions or less, we recommend giving characters an Advance after each session.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Long Campaigns:</span> Grant an Advance after every two or three sessions for a long campaign, slowing it down to every four or five sessions once the heroes hit Heroic Rank.</li><li><span class=\"list-heading\">Milestone Campaigns:</span> Grant an Advance after certain objectives are met in the campaign. You can grant Advances a bit more often in the early stages, slowing things down in the middle and later chapters.</li></ul><h2>Allies &amp; Advancement</h2><p>Followers and other allies who stay with the party for extended periods can improve their abilities as well.</p><p>If the party advances and the Dungeon Master feels the allies have played a significant role in the story, they Advance as well. This gives player characters a group of loyal retainers and hirelings to interact with and deepens immersion.</p><p>You’ll find an Ally Sheet on our website the group can fill in and use to keep up with their retainers' profile, gear, history, and other notes.</p></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":800000,"name":"Langauges","type":"text","_id":"GExl4xVmMPGHeLpt","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><h1 class=\"wide\">Languages</h1><p>In Eberron, languages reflect culture and geography; a dwarf raised in @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Breland]{Breland} might not know Dwarvish, but a halfling raised in the Mror Holds might. The historical development of languages and cultures also explains the scripts used to write various languages. For example, the Orc language is written using the Goblin script, because the orcs of Khorvaire learned writing from the goblins. Common is the language of the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Five Nations]{Five Nations} and the language of trade in Khorvaire, known by most of its people. Goblin was the trade language of the goblin empire of Dhakaan and survives as the primary language in @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Darguun]{Darguun}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Droaam]{Droaam}, and the Shadow Marches. Goblin displaced the Orc language; the people of the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Shadow Marches]{Shadow Marches} typically speak Goblin, and Orc is an exotic language. Members of all races in @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Xen'drik]{Xen'drik} speak Giant and use it as their trade language. Infernal is the common tongue of all fiends, while Celestial is \"the tongue of Siberys.\"</p><h2>Welcome to Eberron</h2><p>With the DM's approval, you can exchange a language granted by your race for a different language from the Standard Languages of Eberron table. If your halfling was raised in the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Mror Holds]{Mror Holds}, you might replace Halfling with Dwarvish to reflect that background. The DM may change the languages assigned to a monster or NPC. An ogre from @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Droaam]{Droaam} likely speaks Goblin instead of Giant.</p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Standard Languages</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Language</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Typical Speakers</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Script</th></tr><tr><td>Common</td><td>Citizens of Khorvaire</td><td>Common</td></tr><tr><td>Dwarven</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Mror Holds]{Mror Holds}</td><td>Dwarvish</td></tr><tr><td>Elven</td><td>Aerenal, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Valenar]{Valenar}</td><td>Sylvan</td></tr><tr><td>Goblin</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Darguun]{Darguun}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Droaam]{Droaam}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Shadow Marches]{Shadow Marches}, monsters of Khorvaire</td><td>Goblin</td></tr><tr><td>Gnomish</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Zilargo]{Zilargo}</td><td>Dwarvish</td></tr><tr><td>Halfling</td><td>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Talenta Plains]{Talenta Plains}</td><td>Goblin</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Exotic Languages</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Language</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Typical Speakers</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Script</th></tr><tr><td>Argon</td><td>Barbarians of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Argonnessen]{Argonnessen} and Seren</td><td>Common</td></tr><tr><td>Draconic</td><td>Kobolds, lizardfolk, troglodytes, dragons, arcane uses</td><td>Draconic</td></tr><tr><td>Druidic</td><td>Druids, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Eldeen Reaches]{Eldeen Reaches}</td><td>Draconic</td></tr><tr><td>Giant</td><td>Native inhabitants of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Xen'drik]{Xen'drik}</td><td>Giant</td></tr><tr><td>Orc</td><td>Isolated orc tribes</td><td>Goblin</td></tr><tr><td>Riedran</td><td>People of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Sarlona]{Sarlona}</td><td>Common</td></tr><tr><td>Sahuagin</td><td>Sahuagin, sailors</td><td>Sahuagin</td></tr><tr><td>Khyber's Tongue</td><td>Denizens of Khyber, symbionts</td><td>Daelkyr</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Planar Languages</th></tr><tr><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Language</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Typical Speakers</th><th class=\"sub-heading left\">Script</th></tr><tr><td>Celestial</td><td>Celestials, Archons of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.KI8pzxk9wb1N1r9O]{Shavarath}, couatl, shulassukar</td><td>Celestial</td></tr><tr><td>Daan</td><td>lawful outsiders of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.BhzXimkcRrlZPjsc]{Daanvi}</td><td>Daan</td></tr><tr><td>Infernal</td><td>Beings of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.KI8pzxk9wb1N1r9O]{Shavarath}, Lords of Dust, tieflings</td><td>Infernal</td></tr><tr><td>Irial</td><td>Deathless, energy beings of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.7tUjCpjC6Nugn3ff]{Irian}</td><td>Celestial</td></tr><tr><td>Kythric</td><td>Slaadi, choatic outsiders of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.pgs12ipPyYbHRfhh]{Kythri}</td><td>Daan</td></tr><tr><td>Quori</td><td>Inspired, kalashtar, quori</td><td>Quori</td></tr><tr><td>Primordial</td><td>Elementals</td><td>Primordial</td></tr><tr><td>Sylvan</td><td>Dryads, eladrin, fey of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.8Qr41zEq2UorAcce]{Thelanis} and woodland beings</td><td>Sylvan</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674589342974,"modifiedTime":1674589342974,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
